Personal Life

LaMarche used to work as a stand-up comedian, and quit for the first time in 1987 after the murder of his father at the hands of a lifelong friend. LaMarche ceased work for two years following the incident, drinking heavily and becoming depressed. However, he resumed his work as a comedian in 1989, only to quit again a year later - this time for good - after losing his younger sister in an automobile accident.
name: Maurice LaMarche

description: Andrew Blackman (also known as Rivenis Black) is a self taught artist originally from London, England now working in Barbados. From a young age he was inspired by the visual and surrealistic nature of dreams and seeks to project them into the conscious world using the tools at his disposal. Besides being a prolific illustrator Rivenis is also a skilled writer and merges his two talents to create Graphic novels. His current work is the independently published Diskordia. He also illustrates Bobby Fischer: The Knight who killed the Kings; a graphic novel written and Created by Xenios Theocharous. His work has appeared in several online and printed publications including Ballistic media’s acclaimed Exotique series.
name: Andrew Blackman
